LanguageData.WVC_XaG_SacrificerGizmoTip:
Sacrificer allows to <color=#8a8ae6>edit xenogenes</color>, but it requires <color=#8a8ae6>sacrifices</color>. It automatically sacrifices one <color=#8a8ae6>random pawn</color> every day. The target can be any <color=#8a8ae6>sentient pawn</color>, excluding slaves and temporary ones. Each sacrifice comes with one of the chosen <color=#8a8ae6>rewards</color>.

If the <color=#8a8ae6>victim is human</color>, their genes become available to the sacrificer. The <color=#8a8ae6>complexity limit</color> is increased by 1. If the victim had archite genes, the <color=#8a8ae6>archite limit</color> is also increased.

If the victim was not human, the <color=#8a8ae6>metabolic limit</color> is increased by 1 in both directions instead of complexity and archite.

 - <color=#aad8a2>Unlocked genes</color>: {0}
 - <color=#8076ff>Complexity limit</color>: {1}
 - <color=#8076ff>Archite limit</color>: {2}
 - <color=#8076ff>Metabolic limit</color>: From {3} to {4}
 - <color=#FFDC72>Reward mode</color>: {5}
